\n At some point during development, you might make a mistake that results in an error or issue in the client application. In such cases, you\u2019ll need to check the server log, identify the error, and correct it. \n In this guide, we\u2019ll use the server log/console via the Docker application. \n   Viewing the log in Docker \n In Docker, click on the name of your container and go to  Logs . What you see here is actually the Server console, which includes various information, including error logs. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4e18098db7d9a86bcaa50778bf8867406d8f1b9d.png]\nDescription: The image displays the Docker Desktop interface, specifically focused on the \u0022myapplication\u0022 container under the \u0022Containers\u0022 section. The visible UI contains the container ID \u0022797a7d2645ec\u0022 associated with the image \u0022origam/server:master-latest.linux,\u0022 which is currently running. The status of this container indicates \u0022Running (21 minutes ago).\u0022 Key UI elements include a navigation menu with options for \u0022Containers,\u0022 \u0022Images,\u0022 \u0022Volumes,\u0022 \u0022Builds,\u0022 \u0022Docker Scout,\u0022 and \u0022Extensions.\u0022 The field highlighted is \u0022Logs,\u0022 showing log entries dated \u00222025-03-25\u0022 with timestamps at \u002211:47:31,\u0022 detailing system operations: \u0022Development self-signed SSL certificate files created\u0022 and \u0022Starting nginx: nginx.\u0022\n\n\n  \n Alternatively, if you want to focus only on the server error log directly, you can find it in the server files. On Linux, it is located at  home/origam/HTML5/logs/OrigamServer.log : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/51a5e9a1c81c31852d5753547b2d3de9272830da.png]\nDescription: The image depicts the Docker Desktop interface, specifically the \u0022Files\u0022 tab for a container labeled \u0022myapplication\u0022 with the ID 797a72d645ec. The UI shows a navigation pane on the left, with sections for \u0022Containers,\u0022 \u0022Images,\u0022 \u0022Volumes,\u0022 \u0022Builds,\u0022 \u0022Docker Scout,\u0022 and \u0022Extensions.\u0022 The main content area lists the directory structure for the container, showing files within a \u0022logs\u0022 folder. The visible files include \u0022MailLog.log,\u0022 \u0022MailLog.log20250325,\u0022 and \u0022OrigamServer.log,\u0022 with \u0022OrigamServer.log\u0022 highlighted. The apparent purpose of this interface is to manage container files and logs in a Docker environment.\n\n\n  \n If you want to work with the server log more thoroughly, you can configure Docker to save it to your local computer and open it in a program that helps you read and analyze logs effectively. \n   Analyzing errors \n We won\u2019t go into deep log analysis here but will share some basic tips for identifying and understanding errors. \n Here are a few helpful hints: \n  1. Time  \nWhen an issue occurs in your application, it\u2019s important to note the exact time it happened. This will help you locate the corresponding error in the log. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3af22e0f2886ab411b741c254b386af3dcbd3110.png]\nDescription: The image displays a log output from a server process, showing various timestamped entries related to a software application. Key details include a successful update of the \u0022OrigamSettings.config\u0022 file and a warning regarding Microsoft.AspNetCore.DataProtection. The log captures a critical error on March 27, 2025, at 13:23:56, indicating an \u0022ArgumentOutOfRangeException\u0022 with a data constant/parameter not found, and it includes the actual value as \u0022e 3511.\u0022 Additional entries reference specific services involved in the issue, particularly \u0022Origam.Security.AbstractProfileProvider\u0022 and \u0022Origam.DA.Service.AbstractSqlCommandGenerator.\u0022 The apparent purpose of the log is to provide insight into the application\u0027s runtime behavior and error reporting for troubleshooting.\n\n\n  \n  2. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:55:29"},"vector":[-0.016440025,-0.015491882,-0.0639967,0.0020317764,-0.020342046,-0.028512293,-0.017000852,-0.017432006,-0.035789754,0.029349579,0.032651197,0.0015155557,-0.018895363,0.013527845,0.0058403523,-0.014594212,-0.017829016,0.0075631817,0.015356289,0.0064587165,-0.013304006,-0.022154626,0.06565964,0.016190162,-0.015461314,0.021486716,-0.025200814,-0.03272965,0.047451306,0.018047756,0.0036531216,-0.03485705,0.006659948,-0.014731807,0.0023885784,0.0032421167,0.009981183,0.010989549,-0.030400194,0.018712739,-0.014210618,-0.020711858,-0.034072865,-0.03318324,0.031259283,-0.038157653,-0.00166693,0.0049927486,0.018910214,0.0016627801,-0.047867563,-0.00674657,0.033727657,-0.043513726,0.024726314,0.038438275,-0.025877679,-0.010679388,-0.015960077,0.023232307,-0.023770768,0.014739692,0.007894379,-0.016179409,-0.008439129,0.057449218,-0.0066765635,0.008332739,-0.034461666,0.0011641383,0.01810646,0.033732552,-0.040236827,-0.040658485,-0.064648725,0.01917175,0.028361777,-0.009580488,0.0066683902,-1.5753605E-05,-0.014990906,0.002402762,0.0076093487,-0.030407788,-0.051680848,0.042467955,-0.02326824,0.053113878,0.043139227,-0.00022415399,-0.016246697,-0.019878097,0.028983315,0.0034202877,-0.039244708,0.011398141,-0.01083996,-0.0037885983,0.013534844,0.032393612,-0.008453269,-0.04069064,-0.00077567605,-0.018149173,0.011209571,0.024157284,0.0080755595,-0.0037530437,-0.02518497,-0.037552465,-0.011571953,-0.027434926,0.0030879723,-0.018147064,0.0032806937,-0.013939197,-0.012785391,-0.023882106,-0.010274451,0.025656627,0.0084131975,0.03747944,0.06722951,-0.03428602,-0.025165947,0.048861843,0.013601793,0.039112262,0.037540257,0.0022611225,0.024497315,-0.003939961,-0.008486858,0.026470156,-0.023323074,0.0021958854,0.009602941,-0.007022733,0.02947114